  "text": "The present study reports on a new approach to guide urogynaecologists selecting patients for planned surgical strategies. Following the IDEAL recommendations [CITATION_1] , this refers to Stage 2a, the development level on a small collective of patients. Future prospective studies will address the therapeutic outcome in relation to the sonographic findings in a larger number of patients.",
